First, we need to rearrange the given system of linear equations to isolate x, y, and z:

\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{1}{2}(7 - 3y + z) \\
y &= \frac{1}{4}(3x + z + 12) \\
z &= \frac{1}{5}(x - y + 15)
\end{align*}

Now, we can apply the Jacobi iterative method using the initial guesses $x_0 = 0$, $y_0 = 0$, and $z_0 = 0$. We will perform five iterations:

Iteration 1:
\begin{align*}
x_1 &= \frac{1}{2}(7 - 3(0) + 0) = 3.5 \\
y_1 &= \frac{1}{4}(3(0) + 0 + 12) = 3 \\
z_1 &= \frac{1}{5}(0 - 0 + 15) = 3
\end{align*}

Iteration 2:
\begin{align*}
x_2 &= \frac{1}{2}(7 - 3(3) + 3) = 0.5 \\
y_2 &= \frac{1}{4}(3(3.5) + 3 + 12) = 3.875 \\
z_2 &= \frac{1}{5}(3.5 - 3 + 15) = 3.3
\end{align*}

Iteration 3:
\begin{align*}
x_3 &= \frac{1}{2}(7 - 3(3.875) + 3.3) = 0.7125 \\
y_3 &= \frac{1}{4}(3(0.5) + 3.3 + 12) = 3.95 \\
z_3 &= \frac{1}{5}(0.5 - 3.875 + 15) = 2.725
\end{align*}

Iteration 4:
\begin{align*}
x_4 &= \frac{1}{2}(7 - 3(3.95) + 2.725) = 0.3875 \\
y_4 &= \frac{1}{4}(3(0.7125) + 2.725 + 12) = 3.984375 \\
z_4 &= \frac{1}{5}(0.7125 - 3.95 + 15) = 2.3525
\end{align*}

Iteration 5:
\begin{align*}
x_5 &= \frac{1}{2}(7 - 3(3.984375) + 2.3525) = 0.1840625 \\
y_5 &= \frac{1}{4}(3(0.3875) + 2.3525 + 12) = 3.99453125 \\
z_5 &= \frac{1}{5}(0.3875 - 3.984375 + 15) = 2.280625
\end{align*}

After five iterations, the solution is approximately $(x, y, z) = (0.184, 3.995, 2.281)$ with a tolerance of $\epsilon = 0.001$.
